rComments: I would not recommend taking MAT135 with Dr Emory. She does not explain the material very well and she is a bit disorganized. Also, TopHat is marked for participation and correctness. One good thing about her class is that she is unintentionally hilarious especially her chain rule explanation.

pretty cute with the way she keeps telling us to do hmwk lol. at first she's a bit disorganized, but after a month or so she was able to pick up the pace and engage the class. tophat was not fun, and she made quite a bit of mistakes in the answers, which was very problematic because it lead us to the wrong way. otherwise was okay

She is actually a quite nice professor for MAT135. Although correctness is needed for tophat but it's quite easy to get pass 80% and you can even do tophat without going to class (I heard tophat of other professors' lectures can only be done in the lecture hall). She explains problems clearly, but sometimes she might be too quick for concepts.
Her only problem is that she doesn't give enough time for in-class problems. While other profs of the course don't grade on correctness (only participation), she does.
